						<div class="postbody">I'm kinda in a hurry now so I didn't understand the whole problem yet, but one thing that caught my eye is that you're using a weird non-existent addressing mode in a few places: <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">LDA #CHR0_TableLo,x</tt><br /><br />The character &quot;#&quot; represents immediate values, that is, the argument is supplied in the instruction itself, so immediate addressing can't possibly be indexed, it doesn't make sense. It's really weird if any assembler is even assembling this code without throwing any errors.<br /><br />Anyway, I will take a better look at the rest of the post later and see if I can understand what your asking.</div>

